    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1893-03-03T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1893-03-03T00:00:00-05:00" n="313" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d313">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Lincoln</persName> to Mr.
                                <persName type="to">Foster</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of
                                    the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1893-03-03">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 3, 1893</hi>
                        </date>.
                            (Received March 15.)</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 931.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: With reference to Mr. Foster’s dispatch No.
                        1053, of the 8th ultimo, regarding British pretensions with reference to the
                        Mosquito Reservation in Nicaragua, I have the honor to acquaint you that on
                        the 1st instant I called upon Lord Rosebery at the foreign office and
                        communicated the above-mentioned dispatch to his lordship by reading it to
                        him and, at his request, leaving a copy with him.</p>
                <p>His lordship did not go into the subject further than to say that it would
                        have his attention at once.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Robert T. Lincoln.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
